== Herby Fingerling Potatoes & Roasted Onion ==

Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @herbes de Provence{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings).

Toss sliced onion on a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @balsamic vinegar{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Cinch into a packet and place on baking sheet with potatoes.

Roast on middle rack until potatoes and onion are tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Roasted Brussels Sprouts ==

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Toss on a second baking sheet with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until tender and slightly crispy, ~{18-22%minutes}.

== Bavette Steak ==

While veggies roast, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired
doneness, adding @butter{1%tbsp} to pan after flipping, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Cherry Balsamic Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @dried cherries{1%ounce} and cook, stirring,
until slightly softened, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @cherry preserves{1}, @beef demi-glace{1}, remaining @balsamic vinegar{3%tsp}, @water{1/4%cup},
and any resting juices from steak. Simmer until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Toss together Brussels sprouts and sliced onion (along with any roasting juices from foil packet).

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide veggies, steak, and potatoes between plates. Top steak with pan sauce and serve.

> Your steak dinner as you know it has officially been fancified with French flavors. Le menu: Seared
> bavette cuts drizzled with a savory-sweet pan sauce. For the sides, there are fingerling potatoes roasted
> with herbes de Provence, tender Brussels sprouts, and tangy, balsamic-roasted onion. Beat that, Parisian
> bistros!